  "text": "TiDB implements privilege and RBAC enforcement through a well-structured system centered around the privilege package and integrated with the planner.\n\n**Core Components:**\n\n1. **Privilege Manager Interface** (pkg/privilege/privilege.go): The `Manager` interface defines all privilege-related operations including `RequestVerification`, `RequestVerificationWithUser`, `RequestDynamicVerification`, `ConnectionVerification`, and role management methods like `GetAllRoles` and `FindEdge`.\n\n2. **User Privileges Implementation** (pkg/privilege/privileges/privileges.go): `UserPrivileges` implements the Manager interface and serves as the session-level privilege checker. It delegates to MySQLPrivilege cache for actual privilege verification and supports authentication plugins for custom privilege verification.\n\n3. **MySQL Privilege Cache** (pkg/privilege/privileges/cache.go): `MySQLPrivilege` is the in-memory cache of privilege tables (mysql.user, mysql.db, mysql.tables_priv, mysql.columns_priv, mysql.global_priv, mysql.global_grants, mysql.role_edges, mysql.default_roles). It includes immutable and extended data structures for efficient lookup.\n\n4. **Role Graph Resolution**: The role graph is implemented as `map[string]roleGraphEdgesTable` in MySQLPrivilege. Three key methods handle role resolution:\n   - `FindAllRole()`: Breadth-first search through role graph to find all transitive roles\n   - `FindAllUserEffectiveRoles()`: Filters and returns only granted roles\n   - `FindRole()`: Detects direct edges between users and roles\n\n5. **Request Verification Flow**: Both UserPrivileges.RequestVerification and MySQLPrivilege.RequestVerification check privileges hierarchically:\n   - User-level global privileges\n   - Database-level privileges\n   - Table-level privileges\n   - Column-level privileges\n\n**SQL Statement Privilege Mapping:**\n\nThe planner integrates privilege checking at multiple stages:\n\n1. **PlanBuilder** (pkg/planner/core/planbuilder.go): Defines `visitInfo` struct containing:\n   - `privilege`: Required privilege type (e.g., mysql.SelectPriv, mysql.InsertPriv, mysql.UpdatePriv, mysql.DeletePriv)\n   - `db`, `table`, `column`: Resource scope\n   - `dynamicPrivs`: Optional dynamic privilege names\n   \nPrivileges are added per statement type (SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, CREATE, etc.) via `appendVisitInfo()` and `appendDynamicVisitInfo()`.\n\n2. **Logical Plan Builder** (pkg/planner/core/logical_plan_builder.go): For views and tables, adds specific privilege checks:\n   - SELECT operations: Adds mysql.SelectPriv\n   - INSERT operations: Adds mysql.InsertPriv\n   - UPDATE operations: Adds mysql.UpdatePriv\n   - DELETE operations: Adds mysql.DeletePriv\n   - For views with SECURITY DEFINER: Uses RequestVerificationWithUser() to check definer's privileges\n\n3. **Optimizer** (pkg/planner/core/optimizer.go): `CheckPrivilege()` function verifies all accumulated visitInfo entries via RequestVerification(). Also handles temporary table privilege adjustments via `VisitInfo4PrivCheck()`.\n\n4. **Preprocessor** (pkg/planner/core/preprocess.go): Before table access, checks privileges to prevent leaking table existence information through error messages.\n\n5. **Point Get Plan** (pkg/planner/core/point_get_plan.go): `checkFastPlanPrivilege()` validates fast path optimizations against required privileges.\n\n6. **Expression Codec** (pkg/planner/core/expression_codec_fn.go): `findCommonOrPartitionedTable()` checks privileges when accessing tables in expressions.\n\n**Connection Verification:**\n\nPkg/privilege/conn/conn.go defines `AuthConn` interface for authentication plugin communication during connection establishment, supporting custom authentication mechanisms.\n\n**Privilege Check Flow:**\n\nSQL execution follows this privilege check sequence:\n1. Connection-time verification via `ConnectionVerification()`\n2. Statement planning collects required privileges in visitInfo\n3. Planner preprocessing validates table access\n4. Optimizer calls `CheckPrivilege()` to verify all visitInfo entries\n5. For each visitInfo: RequestVerification checks user's role hierarchy and accumulates privileges from global → database → table → column scopes\n6. Dynamic privileges (BACKUP_ADMIN, RESTORE_ADMIN, etc.) are checked separately via RequestDynamicVerification()\n\n**RBAC Implementation Details:**\n\nThe role-based access control uses breadth-first search through the role graph stored in mysql.role_edges table. FindAllRole() starting from a user's active roles discovers all transitive role memberships. Privileges are accumulated from all roles in the effective role set, enabling hierarchical privilege inheritance."
}

